{
  "texts": [
    "Suitable for users at disparate locations needing later database consolidation, our solution provides an HL7 export function for this purpose.",
    "Challenges in scenarios 2 and 3 may involve ensuring data consistency and integrity when merging data from multiple users and databases, necessitating clear data management and validation rules.",
    "In scenarios where multiple users are working on the same database, there is the potential for data conflicts when modifying, adding, or deleting the same data.",
    "A possible solution to this problem is to implement a locking mechanism for individual subjects or visits.",
    "When a user is editing, the data would be set to \"read-only\" for other users; this feature is currently under development."
  ]
}